32:13.099 --> 32:16.561
♪ It's a hard rain... ♪

32:16.728 --> 32:18.813
♪ A-gonna fall. ♪

36:59.385 --> 37:01.220
Zorya Vechernyaya.

37:02.430 --> 37:05.099
He don't going to be happy
to see you.

37:18.195 --> 37:20.531
Organic bullshit.

37:30.291 --> 37:33.336
Of course you come
after I do shopping.

37:33.502 --> 37:35.421
Now I have to send back to store

37:35.588 --> 37:37.465
to make enough for tonight
for supper.

37:37.632 --> 37:39.216
You bad news.

37:39.383 --> 37:42.053
I only come when matters are vital,
as they are now.

37:42.219 --> 37:45.806
God, you are gorgeous.

37:45.973 --> 37:47.725
You have not aged. Hm?

37:47.892 --> 37:50.603
And I brought you a present.

37:50.770 --> 37:54.315
And...for your sister.

37:54.482 --> 37:56.984
And for your sister.

38:06.202 --> 38:08.955
Zorya Ultrennyaya!

38:09.121 --> 38:10.498
She is awake.

38:10.665 --> 38:12.625
Our other sister
is still asleep.

38:15.127 --> 38:18.047
Something to warm
your bedside table.

38:18.214 --> 38:19.590
Our guests stay for dinner.

38:19.757 --> 38:21.133
Go back to store.

38:21.300 --> 38:24.261
A roast, six potatoes,
a rye loaf with seeds.

38:24.428 --> 38:26.180
No seeds, take the wheat.

38:26.347 --> 38:29.225
- I can help.
- You sit. You are guest.

38:29.392 --> 38:31.060
Coffee first.

38:32.853 --> 38:37.775
The Zorya sisters
always make a marvellous home.

38:37.942 --> 38:40.319
We do OK.
We pay rent on time even.

38:40.486 --> 38:42.780
We make some money
from the slaughterhouse.

38:42.947 --> 38:45.241
My sister and I make
a dollar here, a dollar there

38:45.408 --> 38:46.742
reading fortune.

38:46.909 --> 38:48.661
I make the most, of course.

38:48.828 --> 38:50.913
It's because you tell
the prettiest lies.

38:51.080 --> 38:53.040
The truth is not
what people want to hear.

38:53.207 --> 38:56.043
Prettiest woman,
prettiest lies.

38:57.169 --> 38:59.505
Oh, black as night,

38:59.672 --> 39:01.215
sweet as sin.

39:05.344 --> 39:07.847
You take coffee,
then I read your future.

39:08.014 --> 39:10.641
You want from me.
My sisters are garbage.

39:12.309 --> 39:15.187
You do not believe in fortunes.

39:16.272 --> 39:17.732
I think that...

39:17.898 --> 39:19.900
..we're all fucked
any way it comes out.

39:20.067 --> 39:21.444
You know? So...

39:21.610 --> 39:24.155
Seeing that before it happens
is just playing the odds.

39:25.614 --> 39:29.285
Ha! You go sit, be comfortable.

39:29.452 --> 39:31.328
Washroom is second door,
not third.

39:31.495 --> 39:33.205
The third you do not touch.

39:33.372 --> 39:35.166
My other sister
is sleeping inside.

39:35.332 --> 39:38.335
- She needs her rest.
- Is she sick?

39:45.426 --> 39:47.845
He does not know our world.

39:49.180 --> 39:50.848
I'm easing him in.

39:51.015 --> 39:53.517
You are worst man
I have ever seen.

40:34.892 --> 40:38.187
- That smell.
- We have guest.

40:38.354 --> 40:40.439
We have two guests.

40:43.818 --> 40:46.195
Oh. Votan!

40:46.362 --> 40:49.240
Nice to see you, Czernobog,
old friend.

40:49.406 --> 40:50.908
I brought a gift.

40:56.455 --> 40:58.499
Yeah?

41:00.876 --> 41:03.629
And some of that herb Havarti
you like so much.

41:03.796 --> 41:05.923
Why is he in my home?

41:06.090 --> 41:08.592
Make him not be here
or I make him not be here.

41:08.759 --> 41:11.637
I already invite him for dinner.
I cannot uninvite.

41:11.804 --> 41:14.348
I come here only to share
bread and information.

41:14.515 --> 41:17.476
What you choose to do with the latter
is entirely up to you.

41:17.643 --> 41:19.979
Already he's spitting on my rug.

41:20.146 --> 41:21.647
Just a few moments
of your time,

41:21.814 --> 41:23.858
while my man here
helps the ladies

41:24.024 --> 41:25.943
prepare a delicious meal,
I'm sure.

41:26.110 --> 41:28.195
For old times' sake.

41:30.364 --> 41:32.366
Hm?

41:37.288 --> 41:38.789
Make dinner first.

42:04.899 --> 42:07.818
- I'd be happy to help.
- I murder you first.

42:09.987 --> 42:11.447
Think your husband
might beat you to it.

42:11.614 --> 42:14.116
Czernobog is nobody's husband.
I'm nobody's wife.

42:14.283 --> 42:15.659
Relatives.

42:15.826 --> 42:18.704
We come over here together
long time ago.

42:18.871 --> 42:22.458
Family is who you survive with
when you need to survive.

42:22.625 --> 42:25.419
Even if you do not like them.

42:27.922 --> 42:29.340
Everything looks great.

42:29.506 --> 42:31.425
Meat will be tough,
potatoes will be soft.

42:31.592 --> 42:33.010
I am not a good cook.

42:33.177 --> 42:35.387
When I was young,
there were servants to make meals.

42:35.554 --> 42:37.056
Here, there are no servants.

42:37.223 --> 42:40.726
There's only us,
and learning is beneath me.

42:50.945 --> 42:52.696
Thought you were supposed
to read tea leaves.

42:52.863 --> 42:55.532
Tea is disgusting.

43:02.414 --> 43:04.750
So what does it say?

43:10.297 --> 43:12.424
You will have a long life

43:12.591 --> 43:15.427
and a happy one,
with many children.

43:18.138 --> 43:20.724
That bad, huh?
Any good news?

43:20.891 --> 43:23.310
Your mother die of cancer.

43:25.729 --> 43:27.147
Yeah.

43:27.314 --> 43:30.025
You no die of cancer.

43:34.989 --> 43:36.907
Can you get out?

43:37.074 --> 43:38.701
I want you to get out

43:38.867 --> 43:40.536
and take your man with you.

43:40.703 --> 43:42.830
- Or I will break him open...
- Shh!

43:42.997 --> 43:44.748
..and I will choke you slowly...

43:44.915 --> 43:47.251
- Shh!
- ..with his heart.

43:47.418 --> 43:48.669
I'm not going with you
anywhere!

43:48.836 --> 43:50.170
- Shh!
- What's the matter?

43:50.337 --> 43:53.841
Let her wake up -
let your sister hear this con man,

43:54.008 --> 43:55.926
this sonofabitch,
come into my home

43:56.093 --> 43:59.054
and try to make me die.

43:59.221 --> 44:01.557
You brought that madness
into my life once.

44:01.724 --> 44:04.852
- Never again.
- They'll all be there.

44:05.019 --> 44:09.189
Everyone except you.

44:09.356 --> 44:12.234
Each of them thinking
they know what strong is.

44:12.401 --> 44:15.446
And if you're not there
to show them otherwise...

44:15.612 --> 44:18.365
They respect you.

44:18.532 --> 44:21.577
- They KNOW you.
- No, no, they don't know me.

44:21.744 --> 44:24.121
YOU know me.

44:24.288 --> 44:26.790
You know
what these hands have done.

44:26.957 --> 44:29.376
You don't want me,
you want my brother

44:29.543 --> 44:31.462
and he's not here.

44:31.628 --> 44:33.130
Then we'll die.

44:34.256 --> 44:37.259
It will be glorious,
win or lose.

44:37.426 --> 44:39.970
I'm tired of glorious.

44:40.137 --> 44:41.722
Is something wrong?

44:41.889 --> 44:45.267
Nothing at all, my sister.
Go back to sleep.

44:45.434 --> 44:47.478
I'm not successful.

44:49.730 --> 44:53.233
- We should go.
- You said you needed him.

44:53.400 --> 44:54.943
- There's always another way.
- No, no.

44:55.110 --> 44:56.779
No, no. Food is cooked.

44:56.945 --> 45:01.033
Zorya Vechernyaya
invited you for dinner, right?

45:02.076 --> 45:04.370
So you stay and you eat.

45:04.536 --> 45:07.289
Otherwise, she will be insulted.

45:07.456 --> 45:09.416
You understand?

45:09.583 --> 45:11.293
And if you want to leave after,

45:11.460 --> 45:13.712
I will hold open the door.

45:24.807 --> 45:27.017
Mm! Mm...

45:28.268 --> 45:29.353
Mm.

45:30.479 --> 45:32.022
Mm.

45:33.732 --> 45:37.069
Mm. Mm! Delicious.

45:37.236 --> 45:40.948
To think I nearly missed
this fabulous meal, hm?

45:41.115 --> 45:43.659
Thank you, ladies. Shadow.

45:43.826 --> 45:45.661
My old friend, hm?

45:47.538 --> 45:48.705
Ah!

45:48.872 --> 45:50.541
You're black.

45:50.707 --> 45:52.584
Right?

45:54.711 --> 45:56.255
That a problem?

45:56.422 --> 46:01.176
Ehh, we never much care about skin
like the Americans.

46:01.343 --> 46:04.304
Where we're from,
everyone has the same colour,

46:04.471 --> 46:08.725
so we must fight over shades.

46:08.892 --> 46:10.394
Hm.

46:11.437 --> 46:14.940
You see, my brother
had light hair and beard.

46:15.107 --> 46:16.567
Me dark, like you.

46:16.733 --> 46:19.445
I was like the black man
over there.

46:20.487 --> 46:23.449
As against my brother,
the white.

46:25.159 --> 46:28.620
Everybody thought
he must be the good one.

46:28.787 --> 46:30.456
Yeah.

46:30.622 --> 46:33.459
So I became me.

46:33.625 --> 46:37.880
But time passes. Now I'm grey.

46:38.046 --> 46:42.092
Yeah, he too, I...
I believe now is grey.

46:42.259 --> 46:43.760
So you wouldn't be able
to tell

46:43.927 --> 46:47.431
who is light, who is dark.

46:47.598 --> 46:51.310
So much
for fighting over colour.

46:53.103 --> 46:57.232
Yeah, you see,
when we came to America,

46:57.399 --> 46:59.234
we first came to New York.

46:59.401 --> 47:01.695
Everyone first come to New York.

47:01.862 --> 47:04.364
New York was...
Yeah, it was alright.

47:04.531 --> 47:05.949
Sometimes even good, right? Eh?

47:06.116 --> 47:09.244
And then we came here, Chicago,
everything became bad.

47:11.413 --> 47:13.916
I think in old country,
you know, I am forgotten.

47:14.082 --> 47:16.710
Here, I'm like a bad memory.

47:16.877 --> 47:20.672
So I had to find work

47:20.839 --> 47:24.760
and I found meat business.

47:24.927 --> 47:27.513
- You know it?
- I know the eating part.

47:27.679 --> 47:29.556
I know the killing.

47:34.478 --> 47:38.106
So I got job on killing floor
as a knocker.

47:38.273 --> 47:40.025
It was a good job.

47:40.192 --> 47:42.277
Yeah, skilled labour.

47:42.444 --> 47:46.281
A cow comes up the ramp.
Boom, boom, boom.

47:46.448 --> 47:48.158
And you take a sledgehammer
and boop!

47:48.325 --> 47:52.871
You knock the cow dead.
It takes strength.

47:53.038 --> 47:55.415
No cow-killing stories
during dinner.

47:55.582 --> 47:59.294
How do you think
meat get on your plate? Huh?

48:01.129 --> 48:02.881
It takes strength,

48:03.048 --> 48:05.342
but not only strength.

48:05.509 --> 48:07.386
It takes talent,
because it's a craft.

48:07.553 --> 48:09.054
You have to do it right

48:09.221 --> 48:11.181
or the cow gets angry.

48:11.348 --> 48:13.433
And angry meat taste bad.

48:14.643 --> 48:17.604
Yeah, you need arms
to break the skull,

48:17.771 --> 48:19.398
but that's not the goal.

48:19.565 --> 48:22.609
The goal is to crush
the brain inside the skull

48:22.776 --> 48:25.779
and quick,
before the pain can travel

48:25.946 --> 48:27.948
from outside the brain
to the inside,

48:28.115 --> 48:30.659
so the brain never knows
the brain is crushing.

48:30.826 --> 48:34.621
To give a good death is art.

48:34.788 --> 48:37.124
But nowadays,
they have this bolt gun.

48:37.291 --> 48:39.293
You know?
Put it on the forehead.

48:40.877 --> 48:43.297
Yeah.

48:43.463 --> 48:46.133
Now every monkey with a thumb
can kill.

48:46.300 --> 48:48.927
They sit there
all day, all night.

48:53.724 --> 48:56.059
Yeah.

48:56.226 --> 48:58.687
So much for killing.

48:58.854 --> 49:01.940
Hey, do you know checkers?

49:07.863 --> 49:10.407
I was in prison
for three years.

49:12.951 --> 49:16.163
Yeah, people go crazy
for chess.

49:16.330 --> 49:17.748
But you know what?

49:17.914 --> 49:20.584
Checkers is honest.

49:20.751 --> 49:21.627
Hm.

49:21.793 --> 49:24.838
- Every man's an equal.
- Eh, exactly.

49:25.005 --> 49:26.840
After you finish eating,

49:27.007 --> 49:29.009
maybe you and I play checkers.

49:30.761 --> 49:34.473
I shall play black.

49:34.640 --> 49:36.558
Is good?

49:36.725 --> 49:38.310
- Is good.
- Yeah.

49:38.477 --> 49:40.354
I like it. Confident.

49:42.314 --> 49:44.858
Maybe we even bet a little, huh?

49:45.025 --> 49:48.028
You don't have to play him.

49:48.195 --> 49:50.864
What do you say?

49:54.618 --> 49:56.578
You guys play a lot of checkers?

49:56.745 --> 49:59.039
Oh, the sisters don't play.

49:59.206 --> 50:03.085
But I keep sharp,
not like my arms.

50:03.251 --> 50:05.629
They don't get the work-out
they used to, huh?

50:05.796 --> 50:07.798
No more killing floor

50:07.964 --> 50:09.549
to swing my hammer.

50:12.386 --> 50:13.387
Hm.

50:13.553 --> 50:17.057
First blood is mine.

50:19.726 --> 50:22.312
So you've lost. Game is done.

50:24.981 --> 50:27.526
I just started.

50:27.693 --> 50:29.194
Hm.

50:30.987 --> 50:33.448
Confident.

50:38.328 --> 50:40.205
You want to see it?

50:41.248 --> 50:42.416
See what?

50:42.582 --> 50:44.960
The hammer.

50:46.837 --> 50:49.840
The one I used to kill.

50:59.057 --> 51:01.810
It's dull now, but...

51:01.977 --> 51:05.981
..the secret to keeping it clean
is use.

51:06.148 --> 51:08.525
Yeah, blood feeds it,

51:08.692 --> 51:11.528
gives it shine.

51:12.821 --> 51:16.074
You know, the best blood
flows at sunrise,

51:16.241 --> 51:20.412
when the cattle
is rested, fed and calm.

51:20.579 --> 51:24.666
Oh,
now my hammer is red...

51:24.833 --> 51:26.668
..with rust.

51:26.835 --> 51:30.380
No more sunrise blood.

51:36.052 --> 51:41.266
10,000 deaths made right here.

51:56.364 --> 51:58.867
Are you gonna play or what?

52:00.076 --> 52:01.995
It's your move.

52:13.673 --> 52:14.966
Your move.

52:18.345 --> 52:23.517
Hey, we make a wager
on our little game, huh?

52:23.683 --> 52:28.104
You relax.
This is not your game, OK?

52:28.271 --> 52:30.357
You see, your master
wants me to come with him

52:30.524 --> 52:33.568
to deal with his nonsense.

52:33.735 --> 52:36.988
Well...

52:37.155 --> 52:39.574
Listen, if I lose...

52:40.867 --> 52:44.287
..I will go with Votan
and do what he asks

52:44.454 --> 52:47.332
and I will nod
in front of the others.

52:47.499 --> 52:50.126
And if you win?

52:50.293 --> 52:53.255
I get to knock your brains out
with my hammer.

52:56.925 --> 52:59.177
But first, you have to
go down on your knees

52:59.344 --> 53:01.888
and I will hit you
with this.

53:02.931 --> 53:04.516
Just one blow.

53:07.435 --> 53:09.354
Right here.

53:09.521 --> 53:11.648
Sunrise blood.

53:11.815 --> 53:13.483
Is good?

53:18.238 --> 53:20.282
He'll take that shot.

53:20.448 --> 53:24.703
No joke, no boast,
no half-measures.

53:26.746 --> 53:28.874
How good are you?

53:30.750 --> 53:32.586
How bad do you need him?

53:35.380 --> 53:37.173
It's your decision.

53:50.145 --> 53:53.273
Alright, if...
if all this is real

53:53.440 --> 53:57.319
and...and...and TVs talk

53:57.485 --> 53:59.529
and she can read fortunes

53:59.696 --> 54:01.406
and hammers bleed,

54:01.573 --> 54:04.242
and if there is a world...

54:05.869 --> 54:07.662
..under a world...

54:14.419 --> 54:16.087
Yo, fuck it.

54:17.881 --> 54:19.466
Is good.

54:19.633 --> 54:21.259
Is good?

54:21.426 --> 54:23.011
Yeah.

54:23.178 --> 54:25.138
Good.

54:25.305 --> 54:28.850
Your move.

55:27.283 --> 55:30.453
♪ My love made

55:30.620 --> 55:33.748
♪ The sweetest coffee... ♪

55:35.750 --> 55:40.839
♪ With no sugar at all... ♪

55:42.549 --> 55:45.969
♪ She only stirred

55:46.136 --> 55:49.764
♪ With her spoon

55:49.931 --> 55:53.810
♪ And it was done

56:04.029 --> 56:06.990
♪ Now my drink

56:07.157 --> 56:10.702
♪ Is bitter

56:10.869 --> 56:14.122
♪ The secret of spoons

56:14.289 --> 56:17.834
♪ Forgotten

56:19.127 --> 56:22.505
♪ When my voice breaks

56:22.672 --> 56:24.507
♪ On this song

56:24.674 --> 56:29.596
♪ Remember old love gone... ♪

56:39.773 --> 56:41.357
♪ And drink

56:41.524 --> 56:45.904
♪ Your bitter coffee... ♪

56:48.948 --> 56:50.950
♪ And drink it

56:51.117 --> 56:56.748
♪ Bitter co-of-fee. ♪

57:06.049 --> 57:08.635
So at sunrise,

57:08.802 --> 57:12.097
I get to knock your brains out.

57:14.140 --> 57:16.726
And you will go down
on your knees...

57:16.893 --> 57:19.104
..willingly.

57:20.688 --> 57:22.398
Is good?

57:24.359 --> 57:26.402
A shame.

57:28.404 --> 57:30.698
You're my only black friend.
